President Obama has proclaimed October 2015 as National Energy Action Month. The proclamation highlights the importance of energy efficiency, clean power, and working together to preserve the environment for future generations. The United States has made significant advances in recent years, becoming the top producer of oil and natural gas and transitioning towards clean energy sources like wind and solar. The President emphasizes the need to address climate change and reduce carbon emissions, and outlines the measures taken by the US government to cut emissions and increase the use of renewable energy. The proclamation calls upon citizens to work together to achieve greater energy security, a stronger economy, and a healthier environment.